description: Re:NewCell AB engages in the provision of an alternative raw material for textile production. The company is headquartered in Stockholm, Stockholm and currently employs 24 full-time employees. The company went IPO on 2020-11-26. The firm offers a dissolving pulp for textile production manufactured from 100 per cent recycled textiles. Renewcell provides an alternative raw material for textile production that replaces resource-intensive material, such as cotton, or petroleum-based material, such as polyester.
